CatDescriptText: Mrs. Emily Williams, 1202-1/2 N. Murtland Street, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 8, 1958, pg. 2 with question: "Should jitney drivers be licensed and permitted to operate, or should they be jailed?" answer reads: "Yes, because you get better service."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Emily Williams wearing coat with four buttons and fur collar, standing with eyes closed and hands in pockets in front of marble wall between store windows, including one with display and sign that reads "Neckwear 1/2 Off All Sales Final"
